            <h2>Powered by Fenix Platform</h2>

            <p> An internet-based and scalable system able to meet different user requirements and adaptable to
                support global, regional and national level projects and initiatives. The main goal is to contribute
                to creating a global data sharing network for agriculture and food security by establishing a
                scalable system integrating many different data sources.
            </p>
            <p>
                FENIX adheres to the Open Data initiative and is designed to avail data and technologies to anyone
                as “public good” using free, open-source software and providing data at no cost. We aim at
                facilitating collaboration between countries and organizations to build a wide data exchange and
                analysis network.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="fx-home-content-grid-bottom">
            <br>
            <h2>Main Feature</h2>
            <ul class="home-list">
                <li><em>1</em> Based on Open Source software; no licensing constraints and full redistribution rights</li>
                <li><em>2</em> Using a Service-Oriented Architecture (SOA)</li>
                <li><em>3</em> Extensible: ability to plug-in new functionalities and applications (widgets)</li>
                <li><em>4</em> Designed to facilitate data sharing through web services (APIs)</li>
                <li><em>5</em> Using diversified data collection/upload methods (online data entry; uploads from csv/xls files; mobile apps)</li>
                <li><em>6</em> Able to handle databases, geospatial data (as remote sensing, GIS layers, etc.) and text</li>
                <li><em>7</em> An advanced analytical application with the embedded “R” statistical package</li>
            </ul>
